For this task, I used Google Forms to create a “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” for my batchmates. The form included exactly five questions, covering basic awareness about online safety, cyber threats, and responsible digital behavior. I used a mix of question types, including multiple-choice and short answer, to make the quiz both interactive and informative. After creating the form, I linked it to a Google Sheet to automatically collect and analyze responses. I also shared the form link in my README file and added screenshots of both the form and the response sheet in the task-3-platforms/ folder.

This activity helped me practice creating surveys, organizing data, and presenting information effectively. Academically, these tools are very useful for conducting research, collecting feedback, and analyzing data for projects and assignments. Google Forms simplifies data collection, while the linked spreadsheet helps in easy interpretation of results. Overall, this experience improved my digital skills, enhanced my understanding of data handling, and will support me in future academic work such as surveys, reports, and presentations.
